<br>
Every other class in the game gains power throughout their life cycle as a function of either:<br>
<br>
A.  new spells+ larger mana pool+ increased natural mana regen+ mana regen items<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
B.  Increasing melee effectiveness through increases in skills, items and hit point regen.<br>
<br>
<br>
Guess what the modifiers for bards are?<br>
<br>
Items + level<br>
<br>
That's it.  This is why the bard power curve is linear rather than exponential.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Guess what?  AE nukes don't make targets dead any faster.  Sure, I could claim my AE DoT was doing 120 DPS due to hitting eight targets at once.<br>
<br>
After I reloaded to my bind point, that is.  <br>
<br>
Same situation with AE song healing.  Either your group is getting hit by AE, and taking one heck of a lot more than 12 pts/ tick damage, or they aren't, and the song isn't affecting health at all.<br>
<br>
