A Druid MGB'ing regrowth DOES have an enormous healing potential.  To say it doesn't is completely false.  Bards do that without AA skills or mana, not to mention the fact that it has other benefits to the song and it stacks with other regens.  Regening hp and mana for a raid party indefinitely is a huge benefit.<br>
<br>
To think that adding 25% haste to a group of melee and to yourself isn't effective, then I don't understand what you're looking at.  Bards not only increase their own damage, they increase the damage potential of everyone around them.  This doesn't take into account DS'ing the main tank, or OOS for the casters.  Nor does it take into account the combine effects of melee and mana regen for the nukers.  All for zero mana and alot of wrist damage.  Not to mention they wear plate for protection, which is more than Druids and other pure casters get.<br>
<br>
Thott did alot of work, and I think he's truly concerned for the class he's chosen.  I don't agree with drawing comparisons to a class that can't buff, heal, slow, debuff, melee or whatever else I've missed, and saying you are underpowered in comparison.<br>
